cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.IR 

The paper deals with deep learning models for medical image classification, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of unsupervised domain adaptation (UDA) is also a key aspect of the paper, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The specific application of the method to mammogram images further suggests the sub-category of medical imaging (cs.MM). Finally, the paper also discusses the challenges of clinical validation and real-world application, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) in the medical domain.
